  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR Research and Innovation for Global Health Transformation Call 1: Evaluation and Transfer of mobile whole slide tissue scanners and liquid biopsies to deliver fast and precise diagnosis for improved outcomes of children and young adults with Epstein Barr Virus-driven lymphoma: a joint Tanzanian and Ugandan Paediatric Oncology Network Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. To test two new technologies which, by leapfrogging conventional diagnostic approaches, could bring fast and precise diagnosis of Epstein Barr Virus Lymphoma to sub-Sahara Africa; 
2. To generate viral and tumour sequence information to inform the design of future screening programmes and vaccine development; 
3. To perform a clinical validation of our diagnostic tools and then a controlled before-after study to test whether these speed up diagnosis, increase the number of children diagnosed and treated, and ultimately improve survival compared to gold-standard pathology.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A UK and low- and middle-income country (LMIC) research partnership that aims to test two new diagnostic technologies that can help provide fast and reliable diagnosis for Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) in sub-Saharan Africa.</narrative>
  </description>
